The paper deals with the application of machine learning to discover hidden physics in data, specifically in the context of space fractional differential equations. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the use of stationary covariance kernels, which is a common topic in statistical inference (cs.SI) and spatial statistics (cs.SD). Finally, the paper applies the methodology to real-world examples in finance, which could potentially fall under the category of data science (cs.DS).
